Tragedy was averted on Friday, as a yet-to-be-identified driver escaped death after a Saloon Optima KIA vehicle fell off the very busy Shehu Yar Adua Bridge, opposite the Jabi Lake Mall, in the Federal Capital Territory, FCT, Abuja. It was gathered that the accident occurred at about 10 in the morning. According to findings, the white-coloured car reportedly missed Jabi Lake by a few inches. An official of the Federal Road Safety Commission, FRSC, who reportedly witnessed the accident but pleaded not to be named because he was not authorised to speak on the matter, said the driver lost control due to over-speeding.   Ignore region, focus on performance in 2023, Patriotic…     Gombe CAN faction goes to court, stops inauguration of new…     Kebbi, Pakistan set for bilateral cooperation to boost…   The FRSC officer said: “The driver of the car was running very fast on the speed lane when another car interrupted him and he attempted to veer towards the service lane. - Advertisement - “He, however, lost control as the car swerved off the neck of the bridge and glided dangerously towards the lake and only stopped inches from the water. “The driver of the vehicle came out alive and was taken to a nearby hospital,” the official added, although he did not disclose the name of the hospital. Also a statement issue by the Head Public Relation Unit of the Federal Capital Territory Emergency Management Agency, (FEMA), Nkechi Isa confirmed the incident. The statement added that “The cause of the accident is yet to be ascertained”.